Affordances Affordances "term that refers to the properties of objects -- what sorts of operations and manipulations can be done to a particular object" (D. A. Norman 1988, The Psychology of everyday things). A door affords opening A chair affords support "perceived affordance": the extent to which interface objects suggest their affordance. 2nd revised edition 2013: Signifiers indicate the affordance of an interface object. They need to be carefully designed to be able to do this. User interface elements should be designed in such a way that they clearly indicate their affordances.